[Ada County, the most populous county in Idaho with a population of 392 365 residents in 2010, is located in the southwestern part of the U.S. state of Idaho (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ada_County,_Idaho). The county seat and largest city is Boise, the state capital. A map of Ada County can be found at https://www.google.com/maps/place/Ada+County,+ID. - Mod.ML]

