[2] USA (Illinois)
Date: Tue 28 Nov 2017 04:17 PM
Source: Belleview News Democrat [edited]
http://www.bnd.com/news/local/article186941543.html


Up to 7 schools in Champaign County [Illinois] have confirmed whooping cough cases, with a total of 40 cases so far. The Champaign-Urbana Public Health District confirmed 40 cases of pertussis, 27 of which have been confirmed since mid-October [2017]. Rantoul High School has 20 confirmed cases alone, according to the News-Gazette. The latest confirmed cases involve 2 students in Mahomet, Illinois: A 3rd-grader and 7th-grader have each come down with pertussis, a contagious bacterial disease that can take weeks for recovery. Treatment is a 5-day course of antibiotics, which is often delayed since pertussis starts with symptoms similar to the common cold. Last year [2016] Champaign County saw only 7 cases.

[Byline: Elizabeth Donald]

