[3] USA (North Carolina)
Date: Wed 29 Nov 2017 11:42 AM EST
Source: Fox Carolina [edited]
http://www.foxcarolina.com/story/36953136/whooping-cough-confirmed-at-5-henderson-co-schools


Henderson County Public Schools confirmed [that] 8 students have tested positive for whooping cough at 5 schools. Health officials say they expect more people to come down with the illness before the outbreak is over. "We're expecting to have more cases and at some point that will die down," said Dr. Diana Curran, Medical Director for Henderson County Department of Public Health.

Molly McGowan Gorsuch, a spokesperson for the school district, said the students who tested positive for pertussis attend Hillandale Elementary, Clear Creek Elementary, Bruce Drysdale Elementary, Rugby Middle, and East Henderson High schools.

[Byline: Dal Kalsi, Brookley Cromer]

