[4] Australia (New South Wales)
Date: Fri 24 Nov 2017 8:00am
Source: Gold Coast Bulletin [edited]
http://www.goldcoastbulletin.com.au/news/national/antivaxxers-anger-parents-amid-whooping-cough-outbreak-
on-nsw-north-coast/news-story/b0f07635b3fca13ada570eba1862af99


An outbreak of whooping cough on the state's [New South Wales or NSW] north coast has many parents of sick children infuriated with anti-vaxxers. At least 40 cases have been reported in the past 28 days -- the majority among primary school children living around Murwillumbah and Tweed Heads.

Childhood vaccination rates in the northern NSW local health district are as low as 50 percent in some areas. Northern NSW Public Health Unit acting director Greg Bell said in the past 7 days alone 13 cases of whooping cough were confirmed, and that those represent only a portion of the potentially fatal disease in the community.

[Byline: Clarissa Bye]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
