[Murwillumbah, with a population of 9245 residents in 2016, is a town in far northeastern New South Wales, Australia, just south of the Queensland border, 848 km north-east of Sydney and 132 km south of Brisbane (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Murwillumbah). A map of Murwillumbah can be found at https://www.google.com/maps/place/Murwillumbah+NSW+2484,+Australia. - Mod.ML]

