[5] New Zealand
Date: Fri 1 Dec 2017
Source: Newshub [edited]
http://www.newshub.co.nz/home/health/2017/12/national-warning-after-whooping-cough-outbreak-declared.html


Three young children died in the last outbreak - with hundreds hospitalised. The Ministry of Health (MoH) has issued a warning to New Zealand after declaring a national outbreak of whooping cough. A total of 1315 cases have been reported since the beginning of 2017.

Outbreaks of the disease occur every 3 to 5 years. New Zealand's most recent national outbreak was between August 2011 and December 2013, with about 11 000 cases. Up to 3 babies and young children died during this period, with hundreds needing hospital treatment.

