[6] Canada (British Columbia)
Date: Fri 1 Dec 2017 06:00 AM
Source: Times Colonist [edited]
http://www.timescolonist.com/news/local/schools-battle-whooping-cough-as-island-cases-rise-to-107-1.23109886


Royal Oak Middle School and Prospect Lake Elementary are the latest schools to have a confirmed case of whooping cough. It brings the total number of cases on south Vancouver Island to 107. That's a spike from 79 cases for all of 2016. There were 213 cases in 2015 and 47 in 2014.

In September [2017], 5 schools -- Lansdowne, Central and Shoreline middle schools, as well as Craigflower and Cloverdale elementary schools -- had confirmed or suspected cases of whooping cough. An independent school also had a case.

Pertussis vaccinations are recommended for children at 2 months, 4 months, 6 months and 18 months, in kindergarten and then in Grade 9. The B.C. [British Columbia] Centre for Disease Control reported that last year [2016], 76 percent of 2-year-olds had up-to-date immunizations in Island Health's south Island area. Adults are advised to get a booster shot.

[Byline: Cindy E. Harnett]

