[Vancouver Island, with a population of 759 366 residents in 2011, is part of the Canadian province of British Columbia and is located in the northeastern Pacific Ocean, just off the coast of Canada (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vancouver_Island). The island is 460 kilometres (290 mi) in length, 100 kilometres (62 mi) in width at its widest point. Victoria, the capital city of British Columbia, is located on the island's southern end, where nearly half of Vancouver Island's population live. A map of Vancouver Island can be found at https://www.google.com/maps/place/Vancouver+Island. - Mod.ML

